phase 6/T: auto-refresh all 73 Win32 sidecars via zig build bindings

build.zig previously hand-listed only 10 namespaces for --index and 0
for --structs; the remaining 63 .structs.zig files grown by prior fleet
runs were never refreshed reproducibly. Expand the build-graph list to
cover every currently-committed Win32 sidecar and emit both sidecars
(.structs.zig + .index.zig) per namespace. mod.zig auto-discovery picks
them up downstream without further changes.

Result: zig build bindings now regenerates 146 committed sidecars
deterministically; samples can now look up methods from 63 previously
structs-only namespaces. To add a namespace going forward, just add a
line to win32_namespaces and rerun the step.

Zig 0.16's Io split means build.zig can't yet practically scan the
generated/ directory itself (std.Io.Dir.openDir now needs an io arg
not available at build-graph construction), so the list is maintained
by hand for now.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
